author: desruisseaux
msg: Referencing: rewrite some equation in a way closer to EPSG Guidance Note Number 7, part 2, Version 49.
This has the side effect of bringing the equations meaning closer to a "real world" meaning.
For example the former "t function" is now more clearly related to a part of the Mercator projection
(Note: we define that equation in the parent class because Mercator is considered a special case of
Lambert projection with the equator as the single standard parallel, so we will reuse that equation).
